
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `fwupdmgr` baraye modiriat va update kardan firmware device-ha (mesle laptop, mouse, keyboard, etc.) dar Linux estefade mishavad. Firmware mesle barname-haye dakheli device-ha ast ke kar-haye asasi ra anjam midahand. Ba `fwupdmgr` mitoonid firmware-haye jadid ra download va nasb konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `fwupdmgr get-devices` --> 💻 Namayesh device-haye ghabele update
    🔹 `fwupdmgr get-updates` --> 🔍 Check kardan baraye update-haye jadid
    🔹 `fwupdmgr update`       --> ⬆️ Shoro kardan update firmware
    🔹 `fwupdmgr refresh`      --> 🔄 Update kardan database firmware az internet

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ fwupdmgr get-devices

    🔹 Namayesh listi az device-haee ke mitoonand update shavand.

    $ fwupdmgr update

    🔹 Shoro kardan update firmware baraye hame device-haye ghabele update.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ sudo fwupdmgr update
    [sudo] password for user:
    Updating…             [***************************************]
    Restart required: To complete the update, a reboot is required.

    🔹 In dastoor ba estefade az `sudo` ejra mishavad ta dastresi be system ro dashte bashe, firmware ro update mikone va be shoma khabar mide ke system bayad restart beshe ta update takmil beshe.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `fwupdmgr` command is used to manage and update device firmware (like laptops, mice, keyboards, etc.) on Linux. Firmware is like the internal software of devices that performs basic functions. With `fwupdmgr`, you can download and install new firmware versions.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `fwupdmgr get-devices` --> 💻 Show devices that can be updated.
    🔹 `fwupdmgr get-updates` --> 🔍 Check for available firmware updates.
    🔹 `fwupdmgr update`       --> ⬆️ Start the firmware update process.
    🔹 `fwupdmgr refresh`      --> 🔄 Refresh the firmware database from the internet.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ fwupdmgr get-devices

    🔹 Display a list of devices that can be updated.

    $ fwupdmgr update

    🔹 Start the firmware update for all updatable devices.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ sudo fwupdmgr update
    [sudo] password for user:
    Updating…             [***************************************]
    Restart required: To complete the update, a reboot is required.

    🔹 This command is executed with `sudo` to gain system access, updates the firmware, and informs you that a system reboot is required to complete the update.
